# Event-Granted Card IDs Must Be Strippable

When an event grants a **starter / class permanent magic** card, the `nextId(rng, prefix)` call MUST produce an id that `getStarterBaseId` can strip back to the registered `STARTER_CARD_IDS.X` value. Otherwise the card lands in the player's backpack but **does absolutely nothing when played** (the `resolvePermanentMagic` switch falls through silently).

This is the class of bug that affected йӣ·йңҮеҮ» / жҲҳж–—йј“иҲһ / й“ёз”ІжңҜ / дёҚзҒӯиөҗзҰҸ / `discoverStarterMagic` е…ЁеҘ— (15+ cards) вҖ” all from the same root cause.

## Who is at risk

A card relies on starter-id routing (and therefore needs strippable id) when it has **none** of these higher-priority dispatch keys (see [`registry.ts` `resolveEffectId`](client/src/game-core/card-schema/registry.ts)):

- `potionEffect` вҖ” registered potion
- `heroMagicId` вҖ” registered hero magic
- `knightEffect` вҖ” registered knight effect (e.g. `'recall-equipment'`)
- A `magicEffect` value that is itself a **registered effect id** (e.g. `'honor-blood'`, `'guild-hand-recycle'`)

If `magicEffect` is set to a **description string** like `'ж°ёд№…йӯ”жі•пјҡйҖүжӢ©дёҖдёӘиЈ…еӨҮ...'` (very common for starter cards), routing **falls through to starter-id**. Some cards (`transformStreakStrike`, `flankSlotTempAttack`, `deckTopSwapGold`) explicitly omit `magicEffect` to force starter-id routing.

## The strip rule (`getStarterBaseId`)

```ts
return cardId
  .replace(/-pick-\d+(-[a-z0-9]+)?$/, '')
  .replace(/-evt-\d+(-[a-z0-9]+)?$/, '')
  .replace(/-disc-\d+(-[a-z0-9]+)?$/, '');
```

Strippable shapes:
- `${id}-pick-{N}` or `${id}-pick-{N}-{base36}`
- `${id}-evt-{N}` or `${id}-evt-{N}-{base36}`
- `${id}-disc-{N}` or `${id}-disc-{N}-{base36}`

The leading `-N` digit segment is **required** (defense against false-positive strips on substrings like `-discard-` / `-discover-`).

## вң… Correct patterns

```ts
// Event grant via factory:
[id, rng] = nextId(rng, `${STARTER_CARD_IDS.stunStrike}-evt-1`);
// вҶ’ 'starter-perm-stun-strike-evt-1-{base36}' вҶ’ strips to 'starter-perm-stun-strike' вң“

// Discover seed in event:
[id, rng] = nextId(rng, `${c.id}-disc-1`);
// вҶ’ 'starter-perm-X-disc-1-{base36}' вҶ’ strips to 'starter-perm-X' вң“

// Knight deck factory (pure-digit counter):
id: `${STARTER_CARD_IDS.magicMissile}-pick-901`,
// вҶ’ strips to 'starter-perm-magic-missile' вң“
```

## вқҢ Forbidden patterns

```ts
// Missing -N digit segment вҖ” base36 suffix from nextId won't strip:
[id, rng] = nextId(rng, `${template.id}-evt`);
//                                          ^^^^ BUG
// вҶ’ 'starter-perm-stun-strike-evt-{base36}' вҶ’ DOES NOT STRIP вҶ’ no-op when played

[id, rng] = nextId(rng, `${STARTER_CARD_IDS.undyingBlessing}-pick`);
//                                                            ^^^^^ BUG
// вҶ’ 99% of RNG runs leave letters in suffix вҶ’ DOES NOT STRIP вҶ’ no-op

[_id, discoverRng] = nextId(discoverRng, `${c.id}-disc`);
//                                                ^^^^^ BUG
// вҶ’ no -disc-{digit} segment вҶ’ DOES NOT STRIP вҶ’ entire discover modal yields dead cards
```

## Mandatory checklist when adding/modifying an event-grant code path

1. **Find the `nextId` call** that produces the new card id. Confirm the prefix ends in `-pick-{N}` / `-evt-{N}` / `-disc-{N}` (with the digit segment).
2. **Identify the routing field** the card relies on (`potionEffect` / `knightEffect` / starter-id / etc.).
   - If it's starter-id, the strip must succeed вҖ” write the test below.
   - If it's `knightEffect` with a registered handler (like `recall-equipment`), strip success is irrelevant вҖ” but document this assumption.
3. **Add a regression test** in `client/src/game-core/__tests__/event-grant-starter-perm-magics.test.ts`:
   - Assert `getStarterBaseId(grantedCard.id)` equals the expected `STARTER_CARD_IDS.X`.
   - Assert `PLAY_CARD` actually produces the expected effect (damage, prompt, side effect) вҖ” strip-only assertion is necessary but not sufficient.
4. **If you change `getStarterBaseId`** вҖ” also add cases in the same test file proving:
   - All three suffix shapes (`-pick`, `-evt`, `-disc`) strip correctly.
   - Real wild-card ids like `'curse-discard-hand'` and `'amplify-discover'` are NOT mis-stripped.

## How to spot this bug from a user report

> "Event з»ҷзҡ„жҹҗжҹҗеҚЎпјҢжӢ–еҲ° X еҗҺжІЎжңүд»»дҪ•ж•Ҳжһң"

вҶ’ Suspect this rule. Trace:
1. Find the `APPLY_EVENT_EFFECT` token that grants the card вҶ’ locate the `nextId(...)` call.
2. Compute the resulting id by hand: prefix + `-{base36}`.
3. Run that id through `getStarterBaseId` mentally (or in a quick test). If it doesn't strip to a `STARTER_CARD_IDS.X` value, that's the bug.
4. Confirm the card has no `potionEffect` / `knightEffect` / registered `magicEffect` that would short-circuit the routing.

